President Donald Trump met with Secretary of Defense James Mattis, Deputy Secretary of Defense Patrick Shanahan, and the Joint Chiefs Staff to discuss the Department of Defense's preparedness in case of a potential government shutdown. Trump expressed his commitment to providing increased and predictable funding to support the military and achieve peace through strength. He urged Congress to pass a defense budget that focuses on rebuilding the armed forces, increasing the size of the military, and modernizing capabilities. Trump also emphasized the role of Congress in avoiding a shutdown and stressed the need for quick approval of a budget to ensure national security.